Key Match Events: Al Dawi scored for Libya in the 16th minute.
Nshutiyamagara scored for Rwanda in the 47th minute.
Aldeen Al Qulaib, Arteeba, and Al Badri received yellow cards for Libya in the 34th, 42nd, and 45+4 minutes respectively.
Pre-Game Insights: Libya heads into their first match of AFCON qualifying in good spirits after beating Botswana 1-0 in a friendly match.
Libya has shown improvement under new coach Milutin Micho Sredojevic, with only one loss in 11 matches.
Rwanda aims for a major improvement in this qualifying campaign after finishing rock bottom in the last edition.
Rwanda has been excellent in defense under new manager Torsten Spittler, conceding only one goal in his first six matches.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Libya and Rwanda have faced each other eight times, with Libya winning five times, Rwanda once, and two games ending in a draw.
